This bug is a boot-time parameter parsing issue where `setup_preempt_mode()` returns inverted success/failure codes for `__setup()` callbacks. The bug file itself states: "This bug cannot be reproduced through runtime kSTEP execution since it occurs during kernel boot parameter processing."

The actual preemption mode IS applied correctly (the function calls `sched_dynamic_update(mode)` before returning) — only the return value to the boot parameter handler is wrong. This means there's no observable scheduling behavior difference at runtime.

